00:45:36,590 --> 00:45:39,750
I won't resent you anymore.

525
00:45:41,790 --> 00:45:43,620
So...

526
00:45:47,550 --> 00:45:52,390
I hope you can pass on peacefully.

527
00:46:02,340 --> 00:46:04,860
Thank you.

528
00:46:05,830 --> 00:46:08,370
I love you.

529
00:46:10,620 --> 00:46:15,510
My precious daughter, Se Ra.

530
00:47:30,240 --> 00:47:32,280
Noona, you're here.

531
00:47:32,280 --> 00:47:34,820
Today is your grandfather's

532
00:47:36,040 --> 00:47:38,300
death anniversary.

533
00:47:38,300 --> 00:47:41,490
Everyone's probably waiting for you. What are you doing here?

534
00:47:41,490 --> 00:47:44,740
The grandfather that I never liked.

535
00:47:44,740 --> 00:47:47,950
Are you telling me to act like I liked him?

536
00:47:47,950 --> 00:47:51,600
The people who followed him are still keeping an eye on you.

537
00:47:51,600 --> 00:47:52,990
Even if you don't feel like it–

538
00:47:52,990 --> 00:47:55,940
Noona, I brought the champagne you like.

539
00:47:55,940 --> 00:47:58,890
Sit down. Let's drink.

540
00:48:25,120 --> 00:48:26,820
Noona.

541
00:48:28,160 --> 00:48:30,100
I...

542
00:48:31,160 --> 00:48:33,790
can't forget that day.

543
00:48:35,950 --> 00:48:41,210
The day that you freed me.

544
00:48:41,210 --> 00:48:43,320
That day.

545
00:48:47,600 --> 00:48:49,340
Why did you do that to your friend?

546
00:48:49,340 --> 00:48:52,290
Why did you stab your friends face with a pencil!?

547
00:48:52,290 --> 00:48:53,690
They were laughing.

548
00:48:53,690 --> 00:48:58,490
My friend's story wasn't funny at all but they smiled widely–

549
00:48:58,490 --> 00:49:00,440
Chairman!

550
00:49:01,170 --> 00:49:02,480
Hello.

551
00:49:02,480 --> 00:49:03,630
Who are you?

552
00:49:03,630 --> 00:49:05,440
Who the hell are you?

553
00:49:05,440 --> 00:49:09,480
I'm Kim Hui Yeon, I'm your personal nurse starting today.

554
00:49:09,480 --> 00:49:10,410
Wait outside!

555
00:49:10,410 --> 00:49:12,920
No, Chairman.

556
00:49:12,920 --> 00:49:13,900
What?

557
00:49:13,900 --> 00:49:18,000
If you hit him further, I'll call the police.

558
00:49:20,020 --> 00:49:22,600
It must've hurt a lot.

559
00:49:23,580 --> 00:49:26,270
Should we go to the hospital?

560
00:49:26,270 --> 00:49:29,700
It's okay. This happens all the time.

561
00:49:29,700 --> 00:49:32,590
Does your grandfather often hit you?

562
00:49:34,870 --> 00:49:38,930
My mother and father passed away, just like yours.

563
00:49:39,590 --> 00:49:42,030
Until now...

564
00:49:42,660 --> 00:49:45,000
you must've had a hard time being all alone.

565
00:49:46,010 --> 00:49:50,310
From now on, I'll protect you.

566
00:49:53,710 --> 00:49:57,430
"You'll protect me"?

567
00:49:58,650 --> 00:50:00,400
Yes.

568
00:50:00,400 --> 00:50:02,220
I love it.

569
00:50:03,200 --> 00:50:05,100
Noona.

570
00:50:05,100 --> 00:50:07,770
From now on, will you be my noona?

571
00:50:11,210 --> 00:50:13,870
When I was sad and in pain,

572
00:50:14,560 --> 00:50:17,470
the only person that protected me,

573
00:50:21,740 --> 00:50:23,940
was you.

574
00:50:25,910 --> 00:50:28,220
So...

575
00:50:28,220 --> 00:50:33,300
you'll be by my side until the very end, right?

576
00:50:36,100 --> 00:50:37,850
Yes.

577
00:50:40,310 --> 00:50:42,290
Of course.

578
00:51:06,920 --> 00:51:09,230
Busan Gwangjun 8091?

579
00:51:09,230 --> 00:51:13,280
But why did this get discovered here now?

580
00:51:17,220 --> 00:51:19,410
[Emergency Room]

581
00:51:19,410 --> 00:51:21,400
Why did we come here again?

582
00:51:21,400 --> 00:51:23,190
Remember what Mr. Du Kang said?

583
00:51:23,190 --> 00:51:26,330
There's a suspicious drug in nurse Kim Jeong Wu's locker.

584
00:51:26,330 --> 00:51:27,640
What's this?

585
00:51:27,640 --> 00:51:29,520
Why are you here again in the middle of a night?

586
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:30,490
So Ri.

587
00:51:30,490 --> 00:51:33,230
Oh, right. You lied to your grandmother.

588
00:51:33,230 --> 00:51:36,300
You told her you have a girlfriend and that you went on a date.

589
00:51:36,300 --> 00:51:37,930
Huh?

590
00:51:37,930 --> 00:51:39,520
Oh, yes.

591
00:51:40,150 --> 00:51:43,010
I know you said it was to make grandma feel happier,

592
00:51:43,010 --> 00:51:45,220
but why would you tell a lie that would be discovered so quickly?

593
00:51:45,220 --> 00:51:48,640
What if grandma asks to see your girlfriend?

594
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:50,660
It's not a lie, though.

595
00:51:50,660 --> 00:51:53,230
So Ri, I have a favor to ask.

596
00:51:53,230 --> 00:51:55,300
Can you show me nurse Kim Jeong Wu's personal locker?

597
00:51:55,300 --> 00:51:57,110
There's something I have to confirm.

598
00:51:57,110 --> 00:51:59,160
What are you saying?

599
00:51:59,160 --> 00:52:01,850
You can't just see someone else's locker without permission.

600
00:52:01,850 --> 00:52:03,210
You're talking nonsense.

601
00:52:03,210 --> 00:52:05,700
So Ri, please.

602
00:52:07,600 --> 00:52:12,970
It's really important to me, so help me.

603
00:52:15,020 --> 00:52:17,180
I'm not suppose to...

604
00:52:22,010 --> 00:52:24,980
[Nursing Department (Male)]
[Changing Room]

605
00:52:30,420 --> 00:52:32,100
Anything?

606
00:52:32,680 --> 00:52:36,350
It's already been all cleared out, so there's nothing there.

607
00:52:36,350 --> 00:52:38,370
Are you sure you checked nurse Kim Jeong Wu's locker?

608
00:52:38,370 --> 00:52:41,370
I checked two, three times. It's his.

609
00:52:41,370 --> 00:52:45,430
If there's nothing, at least ask for his address.

610
00:52:45,430 --> 00:52:49,740
Then can you give me his address?

611
00:52:49,740 --> 00:52:53,850
Yeong Min, I understand how you feel.

612
00:52:53,850 --> 00:52:58,190
After your mom passed away like that, I felt awful, too.

613
00:52:58,190 --> 00:53:00,010
So it must be worse for you.

614
00:53:00,010 --> 00:53:02,820
I understand you entirely.

615
00:53:02,820 --> 00:53:10,320
But it seems like you've almost stopped driving your taxi, and you're obsesed with you mom's case.

616
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:14,520
So just drop it and leave things to the police.

617
00:53:17,060 --> 00:53:19,650
I want to,

618
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,390
but I can't.

619
00:53:22,390 --> 00:53:24,050
How come?

620
00:53:24,050 --> 00:53:26,230
What's the reason?

621
00:53:27,790 --> 00:53:31,200
I'll explain it all in the future, so

622
00:53:31,200 --> 00:53:35,080
just this once. Please help me.

623
00:53:36,160 --> 00:53:40,890
Yeong Min, I'm so worried

624
00:53:40,890 --> 00:53:43,180
that something might happen to you too if you keep going on like this.

625
00:53:43,180 --> 00:53:46,930
Miss So Ri is a really good friend.

626
00:53:50,990 --> 00:53:52,940
Don't worry.

627
00:53:54,510 --> 00:53:56,990
Nothing will happen to me.

628
00:53:56,990 --> 00:53:59,080
[Changing Room]

629
00:54:31,750 --> 00:54:33,660
Oppa.

630
00:54:35,770 --> 00:54:39,430
Please find Jeong Wu Oppa for me.

631
00:55:05,870 --> 00:55:07,830
How did you die?

632
00:55:07,830 --> 00:55:10,370
I don't remember.

633
00:55:10,370 --> 00:55:12,140
I was high.

634
00:55:12,140 --> 00:55:15,210
Could Mr. Kim Jeong Wu have...

635
00:55:15,210 --> 00:55:18,570
No! There's no way.

636
00:55:18,570 --> 00:55:21,500
He was so good to me.

637
00:55:21,500 --> 00:55:25,600
Anyway, please find him.

638
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:29,840
I can't leave until I see him.

639
00:55:42,260 --> 00:55:44,720
Ji Hyeon, over here.

640
00:55:53,840 --> 00:55:57,670
As expected, the culprit was Kim Jeong Wu.

641
00:57:04,600 --> 00:57:08,810
Wh-Why is this here?

642
00:57:17,120 --> 00:57:21,850
Ji Hyeon. Please wake up.

643
00:57:21,850 --> 00:57:24,610
It's about time you wake up.

644
00:57:28,580 --> 00:57:30,650
I'm so sorry.

645
00:57:35,440 --> 00:57:38,740
Why is your picture here?

646
00:57:40,110 --> 00:57:45,390
Was the person who killed my mother also...

647
00:57:54,010 --> 00:57:55,760
Ms. Ji Hyeon, what's wrong?

648
00:57:55,760 --> 00:57:57,890
I don't know.

649
00:57:57,890 --> 00:57:59,920
My body feels weird.

